longInfo:
Passport required. 
- Passports and other documents accepted for entry issued to
  nationals of Liechtenstein must be valid on arrival. 
- Nationals of Liechtenstein are allowed to enter with an
  expired passport. The passport is accepted when expired for
  a maximum of 5 years.
- Nationals of Liechtenstein traveling without a passport must
  have a document accepted for entry, valid on arrival.
Passport Exemptions:
- Holders of a National ID Card issued to:
 - nationals of Liechtenstein; 

VISA NOT REQUIRED.

Minors:
- WARNING! In accordance with European Union (EU) Legislation,
  all minors who are nationals of Liechtenstein will be
  expected to hold their own passport or National ID Card
  (where applicable) when departing from Bulgaria, Croatia,
  Cyprus, Romania or a Schengen Member State . 
- All minors who are nationals of Liechtenstein are expected
  to hold their own travel document
